{"lemma":"طُنِّ","slug":"طُنِّ","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27138","","n27142","n27143","n27207"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hum, to buzz, to drone"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ring, to clang"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to move with buzzing sound, to whiz"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tonne, metric ton"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the human body","tags":["collective","obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"load carried on the camel's back between the loads on both sides","tags":["collective","obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bundle of reeds used as a bearing","tags":["collective","obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Onomatopoeic.\n\nFrom English ton and French tonne (“ton”), from Latin tunna.\n\nThe meaning of a bundle of reed is considered from Aramaic טוּנַּס (ṭunnas, “reed”), which is attested once in Jewish Literary Aramaic and agrees with Ancient Greek δόναξ (dónax, “reed”), otherwise compare אֲטוּנָא (ʔăṭūnā), אֲטְוָנָא (ʔăṭwānā, “twisted strap”), which occurs in Jewish Babylonian Aramaic sometimes without the aleph prothesis.\nThe meaning of a load, as which also the human body is easily understood, is from the common Aramaic טוּנָא (ṭūna, ṭunnā), an assimilated form of טְוּעֲנָא (ṭūʕănā), טְעוּנָא (ṭəʕūnā, “load, burden”), which or a similar form is also the source of طَاعُون (ṭāʕūn, “plague”)."},"ipa":["/tˤann/","/tˤunn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27138","headword_ar":"طَنَّ","root":"Tn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (MA, Msb, K, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaniynN","text_ar":"طَنِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v. infrà], (MA, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It made a sound"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a continued"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a reiterated kind, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"low"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (MA, Msb, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tn~n","text_ar":"طنّن","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TanoTana","text_ar":"طَنْطَنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tan~a Al*~ubaAbu","text_ar":"طَنَّ الذُّبَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TanoTana","text_ar":"طَنْطَنَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dan~a","text_ar":"دَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danodana","text_ar":"دَنْدَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The flies made a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"humming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"buzzing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sound."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, Msb.) And in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tan~a","text_ar":"طَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said of other things than flies. (Msb.) [Thus,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tan~a AlT~asotu","text_ar":"طَنَّ الطَّسْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tan~ati AlT~asotu","text_ar":"طَنَّتِ الطَّسْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The basin of brass"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other metal made a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ringing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tinkling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sound."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, MA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaT~apu taTin~u","text_ar":"البَطَّةُ تَطِنُّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The duck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goose, utters a sound"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sounds"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quacks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tan~a *ikoruhu fiY AlbilaAdi","text_ar":"طَنَّ ذِكْرُهُ فِى البِلَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His fame resounded through the countries"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tan~at","text_ar":"طَنَّت"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_ibilu","text_ar":"الاـِبِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels thirsted"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. because thirst is often attended with a ringing, or tingling, in the ears]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tan~ato saAquhu","text_ar":"طَنَّتْ سَاقُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His shank was quickly cut off:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the verb being imitative of the sound of the shank in its falling. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tan~a","text_ar":"طَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"died:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) so in the “ Musannaf ” [of Aboo-'Amr Esh-Sheybánee]. (S.) ―         -b6-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He licked his finger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["MA","Msb","K","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n27142","headword_ar":"طَنٌّ","root":"Tn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[accord. to the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tin~N","text_ar":"طِنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", being there said to be with kesr, but not so in other copies of the K, nor in the TA,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fresh, ripe, red dates, very sweet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and having much flowing juice;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tun~N","text_ar":"طُنٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm. (TA.)       -A2-  Also, [if not a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tun~N","text_ar":"طُنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A half-load, such as is borne on one side of a beast, of cotton that has been separated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loosened, and cleared of its seeds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"from El-Hejeree. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n27143","headword_ar":"طُنٌّ","root":"Tn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bundle of reeds"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"canes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,) or (so accord. to the Msb, but in the TA “ and ”)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of firewood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) thought by IDrd to be not genuine Arabic: and pronounced by the vulgar"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tin~","text_ar":"طِنّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr: (TA:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) [i. e.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tun~apN","text_ar":"طُنَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single reed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cane"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of firewood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a bundle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTonaAnN","text_ar":"اَطْنَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) [or,] accord. to AHn, a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tun~","text_ar":"طُنّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of reeds or canes, and of fresh branches, is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wryqp","text_ar":"وريقة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leafy bundle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put together and bound round, and having flowers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blossoms, and plucked fruits put in the interior thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that is put between the two half-loads that are upon the sides of a beast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, K.) ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stature"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a man]: or, accord. to IAar, (TA,) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"body"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man and of any animal: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTonaAnN","text_ar":"اَطْنَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TinaAnN","text_ar":"طِنَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) whence, he says, the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN laA","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaquwmu biTun~i nafosihi fakayofa bagayorihi","text_ar":"يَقُومُ بِطُنِّ نَفْسِهِ فَكَيْفَ بَغَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one will not rise with his own body: how then with another?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but accord. to IDrd, this is a saying of the vulgar; and he does not think it to be genuine Arabic. (TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tan~N","text_ar":"طَنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n27207","headword_ar":"طَنٍ","root":"TnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having his spleen adhering to his side in consequence of vehement thirst:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a tertian fever, and his spleen in consequence having become enlarged:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, * TA:) or a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having his spleen and his lungs adhering to the ribs on the left side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that, sometimes, they become putrid and black;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but mostly this is the case in camels; (TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TanFY","text_ar":"طَنًى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}